metadata.name: P:O:R:C:E:L:A:I:N
metadata.description:
Behold the porcelain girl of blue and white,
A vision of beauty, a true delight,
With skin as smooth as satin and eyes so bright,
She is a creation of art, a wonder to sight.

Her porcelain form, so fragile and fair,
A true masterpiece, beyond compare,
Her body, a flowing work of art,
With delicate patterns, playing their part.

Handle her with care, for she is so fine,
A work of art, of intricate design,
Her beauty will capture your heart and mind,
A porcelain girl, a treasure to find.

In her eyes, a sense of wonder and grace,
A hint of mystery, her delicate lips,
She invites you to a world beyond this place,
A porcelain girl, a symbol of art and grace.

Take her home, give her a place of pride,
Let her be the centerpiece of your life,
For she is a porcelain girl, a treasure to abide,
A work of art, a wonder to confide.
